news.news: Poeltl recorded 25 points (11-12 FG, 3-3 FT), six rebounds, two assists, one block and one steal over 34 minutes during Friday's 106-97 loss to the Magic.
news.analysis: The Raptors came up short and suffered a nine-point loss Friday, but Poeltl made his presence felt on both ends of the court by posting a loaded stat line. The efficiency in scoring certainly stood out, as Poeltl missed just one of his 12 shots from the floor. This was Poeltl's fourth straight game with double-digit points and/or rebounds. He's averaging 14.3 points, 8.3 rebounds, 3.1 assists, 1.4 steals and 1.3 blocks per game over his last 10 appearances.
